## Verification Judgment

When calling `submit_verification_judgment`, you MUST provide `manual_review` evidence:

```javascript
{
  "task_id": 5,
  "judgment": "PASS",
  "rationale": "All checks passed, implementation matches spec requirements...",
  "manual_review": {
    "files_reviewed": ["src/core/feature.ts", "test/unit/feature.test.ts"],
    "observations": "Implementation uses the builder pattern as specified, includes proper error handling for edge cases...",
    "quality_assessment": "Code quality is good, follows project patterns, tests comprehensive..."
  }
}
```

This prevents "rubber-stamping" — you must actually read the implementation code.

