## Anti-Patterns

### ❌ Don't Do This

```javascript
// WRONG - direct database access
run_command("sqlite3 .orchestra/orchestra.db 'SELECT * FROM tasks'")

// WRONG - shell commands for search
run_command("grep -r 'pattern' src/")
run_command("findstr /s 'pattern' src\\*")

// WRONG - vague acceptance criteria
"Feature works correctly"
"Tests pass"

// WRONG - deferred functionality
"Stub implementation for future work"
"Placeholder that throws NotImplemented"

// WRONG - no context
prepare_task({ ..., context: "Implement feature" })  // Too short, no WHY
```

### ✅ Do This Instead

```javascript
// RIGHT - use MCP tools
get_sprint_status()
get_task({ task_id: 5 })

// RIGHT - use specialized tools
grep_search({ query: "pattern", includePattern: "src/**" })

// RIGHT - measurable acceptance criteria
"slugify('Hello World') returns 'hello-world'"
"All 4 unit tests in test/unit/feature.test.ts pass"

// RIGHT - full implementation required
"Complete working implementation of X per spec section 2.3"

// RIGHT - meaningful context
prepare_task({
  ...,
  context: "Implements the string utility module per F001-F004. Uses pure functions for testability. Slugify follows URL-safe conventions. Truncate includes ellipsis in character count to prevent overflows."
})
```

